01/05/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- The presidents of Afghanistan and Pakistan -- Hamid Karzai and General Pervez Musharraf -- agreed on Monday (April 30th) in Ankara to unite efforts against terrorism.
In a joint statement after the meeting, the two leaders agreed "to deny sanctuary, training and financing to terrorists and to elements involved in subversive and anti-state activities in each other's country, and to initiate immediate action on specific intelligence exchanges in this regard".
The presidents also voiced concern about poppy cultivation and the link between the drug trade and terrorism.
Turkish President Ahmet Necdet Sezer hosted the meeting.
(Zaman, Milliyet - 01/05/07;
AP, Reuters - 30/04/07)
